---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BattleCry from '../components/BattleCry.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {JSON.stringify({
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@type': 'Organization',
      name: 'Journal Foundation',
      url: 'https://journalfoundation.org',
      publishingPrinciples: 'https://journalfoundation.org/privacy'
    })}
  </script>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <BattleCry>
    <div class="hero-quote">
      <p><strong>JournalNet is our flagship encrypted data layer</strong>‚Äîprotocols and tooling so people and organizations can steward sensitive personal data without ceding custody. <a href="/journalnet">Learn about JournalNet ‚Üí</a></p>
      <p><strong>Some data must remain more private than the rest</strong>; ISO 29100 calls it sensitive PII, and today it flows through brokers, platforms, and AI systems that shape us without consent.</p>
      <p>Software is dissolving into intent. Bespoke, disposable apps will sit atop whatever data layer we tolerate. If we hand that layer to platforms, they control us. If we keep it encrypted and sovereign, we decide when and how intelligence meets our memories.</p>
      <p>In a world where intent and data are scarce resources, we insist they stay with the individual and optionally trusted partners‚Äîfriends, cooperatives, or the AI providers we authorize.</p>
      <p><strong>We're building protocols for people to ‚Äúhave‚Äù their data and ‚Äúuse‚Äù it too‚Äîlocal or mirrored vaults, selective accessibility, and frontier LLMs that never inherit surveillance.</strong></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cta-group">
      <a href="/docs" class="btn btn--primary">
        üõ†Ô∏è Build Apps
      </a>
      <a href="/learn" class="btn btn--secondary">
        üìö Learn Privacy
      </a>
      <a href="/governance#funding" class="btn btn--tertiary">
        üí∞ Support Us
      </a>
    </div>
  </BattleCry>
  
  <!-- Three Part Explainer -->
  <section class="explainer-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Why This Matters</h2>
        <p class="subtitle">We're not building another app. We're hardening the data layer so intent and intelligence stay with the sovereign individual.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="explainer-grid">
        <div class="explainer-card card">
          <div class="explainer-number">1</div>
          <h3>The Problem</h3>
          <p>Sensitive personal data leaks into attention markets faster than we can contest it:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Biometric, location, and relationship data get warehoused for resale</li>
            <li>Data brokers transport our personal data to police, advertisers, and political actors</li>
            <li>Platforms and AI systems remix our intent into behavioral nudges</li>
            <li>Frontier models learn from the archives we can't retract</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="explainer-card card">
          <div class="explainer-number">2</div>
          <h3>Decentralization and Openness Are Not Enough</h3>
          <p>Software is becoming disposable. Without encrypted custodianship, the data layer still betrays us:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Metadata still exposed:</strong> Who talks to whom is visible</li>
            <li><strong>Federation centralizes:</strong> Your instance admin sees everything</li>
            <li><strong>Correlation attacks:</strong> Traffic patterns reveal identity</li>
            <li><strong>LLMs read public data:</strong> bespoke agents can mirror and manipulate you</li>
            <li><strong>Post-Quantum decryption:</strong> Download now, decrypt with quantum later</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="explainer-card card">
          <div class="explainer-number">3</div>
          <h3>The Stack Difference</h3>
          <p>Infrastructure for sovereignty, not another social network:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Encrypted by default‚Äîwith local or mirrored custody</li>
            <li>Selective accessibility for the people and AI partners you choose</li>
            <li>Metadata minimization through blind relays</li>
            <li>Self-hostable without compromise</li>
            <li>Open-source data layer for bespoke, swappable apps</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  
  <!-- Stack Explainer -->
  <section class="stack-explainer">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>The Journal Protocol Stack</h2>
        <p class="subtitle">Three layers that enable apps without platforms</p>
      </div>

      <div class="stack-grid">
        <div class="stack-layer">
          <h3>üì¶ Layer 1: Vault</h3>
          <p>Encrypted storage you control</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stack-layer">
          <h3>üîí Layer 2: Cipherlot</h3>
          <p>Capability-based sharing</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stack-layer">
          <h3>üì± Layer 3: Apps</h3>
          <p>Swappable interfaces</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-group">
        <a href="/stack" class="btn btn--secondary">Learn How It Works ‚Üí</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Get Started -->
  <section class="get-started-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>How to Engage</h2>
        <p class="subtitle">Three ways to participate</p>
      </div>

      <div class="explainer-grid">
        <div class="explainer-card card">
          <h3>üõ†Ô∏è For Developers</h3>
          <p>Build intent-driven software atop encrypted personal vaults‚Äîno platform custody required.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Read the specifications</li>
            <li>Try the quickstart guide</li>
            <li>Join technical discussions</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="card-link">
            <a href="/docs">Start building ‚Üí</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="explainer-card card">
          <h3>üìö For Privacy Advocates</h3>
          <p>Teach communities how to protect sensitive PII while still using AI and shared tools.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Learn privacy fundamentals</li>
            <li>Explore the protocol stack</li>
            <li>Share guides with your community</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="card-link">
            <a href="/learn">Visit learning center ‚Üí</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="explainer-card card">
          <h3>üí∞ For Funders &amp; Advisors</h3>
          <p>Support open protocols that keep intent and data sovereign while enabling trusted collaboration.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Review financial dashboard</li>
            <li>See governance model</li>
            <li>Contact for partnerships</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="card-link">
            <a href="/journalnet">Discover JournalNet's roadmap ‚Üí</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero Quote */
  .hero-quote {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(17, 24, 33, 0.85) 0%, rgba(5, 7, 10, 0.85) 100%);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-amber);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: min(900px, 100%);
    text-align: left;
    font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 2.5vw, 1.375rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-quote p {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .hero-quote p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .hero-quote strong {
    color: var(--color-accent-emerald);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* CTAs */
  .cta-group {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .cta-group .btn {
    min-width: min(220px, 100%);
  }

  /* Sections */
  section {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
  }
  
  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }
  
  .section-header h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  
  .subtitle {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  /* Explainer Grid */
  .explainer-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .explainer-card {
    gap: var(--space-2xs);
    border-color: var(--color-border-subtle);
    transition: border-color var(--duration-base) var(--easing-standard),
      background-color var(--duration-base) var(--easing-standard);
  }

  .explainer-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(45, 125, 255, 0.4);
    background: rgba(45, 125, 255, 0.08);
  }
  
  .explainer-number {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    background: rgba(45, 125, 255, 0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(45, 125, 255, 0.45);
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--color-accent-azure);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  
  .explainer-card h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }
  
  .explainer-card ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  .explainer-card li {
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  
  .explainer-card li::before {
    content: "‚Üí";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--electric-blue);
  }
  
  .explainer-card pre {
    background: var(--void);
    padding: var(--space-md);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  
  .explainer-card code {
    color: var(--encrypted-green);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  
  .card-link {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  /* Urgency Section */
  .urgency-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1), rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.1));
    border-left: 4px solid var(--urgent-amber);
  }
  
  .urgency-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .urgency-content h2 {
    color: var(--urgent-amber);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }
  
  .urgency-quote {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  
  .urgency-quote p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  .urgency-conclusion {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }
  
  /* Stack Explainer */
  .stack-explainer {
    background: rgba(45, 125, 255, 0.06);
  }

  .stack-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .stack-layer {
    background: var(--void-lighter);
    border: 1px solid rgba(45, 125, 255, 0.25);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    text-align: left;
  }

  .stack-layer h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .stack-layer p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  
  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cta-group {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
    }
    
    .cta {
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>
